                            p In 2013 I produced the documentary film <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MX3CCcNXGFo"> "Spread the Stoke"</a> for my Thesis Project at McMaster University, Hamilton ON. I won the University Thesis Award for Multimedia with this film about the international female longboard community and found skateboarding after a lifetime of varsity athletics. I won female athlete of the year grade 7, 8 and 9 in Caledon, ON. I competed with McMaster University Varsity Rowing team in 2008/09 and the McMaster Varsity Rugby team in 2009/10 and 2010/2011.
                            | I began Downhill Skateboard racing in 2014 when I moved to BC. I placed 1st in the <a href="https://www.webscorer.com/racelaps?raceid=24942&did=30016&cid=158713"> 2014 Skateboard Biathalon </a> (Skate & Shoot) in Whistler, BC. I enjoyed lots of racing through 2014 to 2016 and am excited to be back in the scene to represent Canada at the 2022 World Skate Games.
